# BMC Cross-Sync Propagation (Calculadora BMC)

When the user asks to **sync the calculadora** with production, **align local and remote**, **verify Vercel + API**, run **smoke prod**, or **cross-sync** changes across the Calculadora stack (`src/`, `server/`, integrations, MATRIZ), read and follow:

`.cursor/skills/bmc-cross-sync-propagation/SKILL.md`

## Scope

- **Production frontend:** `https://calculadora-bmc.vercel.app`
- **Local:** `http://localhost:5173` (Vite), `http://localhost:3001` (API)
- **Remote checks:** `npm run smoke:prod` (and env vars as in root `AGENTS.md`)

This rule complements **Project Team Sync** (`bmc-project-team-sync`): use cross-sync for **Calculadora-focused** propagation and local vs prod verification; use project team sync for full team runs and global PROJECT-STATE protocol.

